{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e9efac9d-06dd-453f-8f97-bbeadafaffa3","content":"This template is **not quite ready** to publish. Here are the issues:\n\n**Missing required field:**\n- `$schema` — recommended for validation: `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"`\n\n**Missing important metadata:**\n- `generatorVersions` — should specify `[1.0.0.0-*]` (or appropriate range)\n- `groupIdentity` — needed if you plan multiple related templates\n- `precedence` — helps NuGet resolve template versions\n- `description` — no description field; users won't know what this template does\n- `defaultName` — the default project name when none is specified\n\n**Recommendations:**\n- Add a `\"description\"` so it shows up meaningfully in `dotnet new list`\n- Add `\"preferNameDirectory\": true` for typical project templates\n- Consider adding a `sourceName` replacement test to confirm it works\n- Verify a `.template.config/dotnetcli.host.json` exists if you want custom CLI argument names\n\n**What's good:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `classifications`, `tags`, and `symbols` are all correctly structured.\n\nThe biggest blocker is the missing **`description`** — NuGet gallery and `dotnet new` both surface it prominently. Add that plus `$schema` and you're in good shape to publish.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d811230c-816a-49a7-ab63-07a333d0fa31","outputTokens":317,"requestId":"A84F:15666D:727E6B1:7E03355:69F15815"},"id":"5b0cdb74-d2fe-4dd1-b662-dd79a0713379","timestamp":"2026-04-29T01:00:16.299Z","parentId":"f01dbd41-2a5d-4d95-a415-e9a1b073b8d3"}
